As it stands @type implies nothing about the outgoing request and simply 
advises the client on what content-type should be expected from a 
response - so this kind of proposal would change how they work today. I 
originally suggested new attributes but apparently adding them to the 
spec is a costly process.

A &quot;SHOULD&quot; constraint might be more appropriate in this instance

- Mike

